  "subject": "Fix for dependency rules file location",
  "commit_message": "Fix for dependency rules file location\n\nmaven versions plugin & enforcer plugins use an xml file for\nrules. This causes problems e.g. if trying to build from within\na submodule directory like runtime-acm, leading to file not found\nerrors. This commit fixes it by embedding the ruleset in the pom\nfile directly (which means some duplication but fixes the issue).\n\nIssue-ID: POLICY-5583\nChange-Id: I40b81258289afd54b5b4082c77baf9b6b7dbe5b6\nSigned-off-by: danielhanrahan <daniel.hanrahan@est.tech>\n",
